{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Silo gives you a single type, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo\/DataSource"},{"type":"text","text":", that handles the full lifecycle of async data: fetching, caching, state tracking, and broadcasting updates to all observers through a reactive "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":" interface."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every configuration decision — TTL, retries, throttling, dependencies — is expressed through a fluent builder, so a data layer reads like a specification:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let postsSource = dataSource(selectedCategory.dependency(.lazy, clear: true)) { category in","    try await api.fetchPosts(in: category)","} onError: { error in","    error is URLError ? .keep : .clear","}",".ttl(.seconds(120))",".autoRefresh(.seconds(30))",".retry(strategy: .exponentialBackoff(maxAttempts: 3, initialDelay: .seconds(1)))",".distinct()",".build()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Silo is built entirely on Swift’s structured concurrency model. All public API is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@MainActor"},{"text":", all types conform to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and thread safety is compiler-enforced — not lock-based.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"What Silo Handles For You","anchor":"What-Silo-Handles-For-You"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Request deduplication"}]},{"text":" — concurrent ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" calls share one in-flight fetch task"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[